==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Algates
<hw>Al"gates</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[<ets>All</ets> +
<ets>gate</ets> way. The s is an adverbial ending. See
<er>Gate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Always; wholly; everywhere.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ulna now he <qex>algates</qex> must forego.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Still used in the north of England in the sense of
⟦ldquo⟧everywhere.⟦rdquo⟧</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By any or means; at all events.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Fairfax.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Notwithstanding; yet.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Algazel</ent>⟦br⟧
